  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2958",
  "title": "Ability to make InstantSearch a controlled component and use searchState props without mounting other components",
  "body": "**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe 🙏**\r\nThere are times I'd like to make the `<InstantSearch />` component controlled and it reads as if you can do so [based on the Search state guide](https://community.algolia.com/react-instantsearch/guide/Search_state.html).\r\n\r\nHowever, you can't arbitrarily pass state to the `<InstantSearch />` component without also mounting a true (or virtual) widget like `<SearchBox />` or `<RefinementList />` algolia/instantsearch.js#2054\r\n\r\n[Example CodeSandbox of this &rarr;](https://codesandbox.io/s/yjwyyjrp49)\r\n\r\n**Describe the solution you'd like 🤔**\r\nI'd like to be able to be able to pass state to the `searchState` prop directly without mounting components like `<SearchBox />`\r\n\r\n**Describe alternatives you've considered ✨**\r\nIf this isn't possible or it's a major lift then I think areas like the [Search state guide](https://community.algolia.com/react-instantsearch/guide/Search_state.html) and [Routing and URLs guide](https://community.algolia.com/react-instantsearch/guide/Routing.html) could do more to clarify this requirement.",
